Section 1:
Act 474 of the Regular Session
1 State of Arkansas As Engrossed: H3/17/25
A Bill
2 95th General Assembly
3 Regular Session, 2025 HOUSE BILL 1598
4
5 By: Representative Brooks
6 By: Senator J. English
7
For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT CONCERNING THE SCHOOL RATING SYSTEM; TO
10 REQUIRE THE DEPARTMENT OF EDUCATION TO ESTABLISH A
11 NEW ACCOUNTABILITY SYSTEM FOR PUBLIC SCHOOLS; TO
12 REMOVE PUBLIC SCHOOLS FROM SCHOOL RATINGS FOR CERTAIN
13 SCHOOL YEARS; AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES.
14
15
Subtitle
16
17 TO REQUIRE THE DEPARTMENT OF EDUCATION
18 TO ESTABLISH A NEW ACCOUNTABILITY SYSTEM
19 FOR PUBLIC SCHOOLS; AND TO REMOVE PUBLIC
20 SCHOOLS FROM SCHOOL RATINGS FOR CERTAIN
21 SCHOOL YEARS.
22
23 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
24
25 SECTION 1. DO NOT CODIFY. TEMPORARY LANGUAGE.
26 (a) The General Assembly finds that:
27 (1) A change in the assessment system for public schools and
28 public school districts in Arkansas was necessary to align with the
29 educational priorities established by Acts 2023, No. 237, also known as the
30 "LEARNS Act";
31 (2) The development of a revised accountability system that
32 includes the new assessment system and better meets the needs of Arkansas
33 students is currently in progress; and
34 (3) A pause in new letter grade designations for the 2023-2024
35 and 2024-2025 school years under the existing school rating system will allow
36 the collection of necessary data to provide accurate and reliable
*TNL243*
03-17-2025 12:25:41 TNL243
As Engrossed: H3/17/25 HB1598
1 accountability information, which is essential for Arkansans to make informed
2 decisions regarding their children's education.
3 (b) The Department of Education shall not assign to public schools new
4 school ratings calculated under the current school rating system under ยง 6-
5 15-2105 for the 2023-2024 school year.
6 (c) The department shall:
7 (1) Establish a new accountability system; and
8 (2)(A) Issue all public schools, including open-enrollment
9 public charter schools, a letter grade for the 2024-2025 school year using
10 the new accountability system established under subdivision (c)(1) of this
11 section.
12 (B)(i) If a public school or an open-enrollment public
13 charter school does not improve or maintain its most recent letter grade
14 under the new accountability system established under subdivision (c)(1) of
15 this section, then the public school or open-enrollment public charter school
16 may request a review by the Division of Public School Accountability.
17 (ii) The division shall review all applicable data
18 and information upon receipt of a request from a public school or an open-
19 enrollment public charter school under subdivision (c)(2)(B)(i) of this
20 section and make a determination regarding the public school's or open-
21 enrollment public charter school's letter grade.
22 (e) This section shall expire on June 30, 2026.
23
24 /s/Brooks
