15
Subtitle
16
17 TO REQUIRE THE DEPARTMENT OF EDUCATION
18 TO ESTABLISH A NEW ACCOUNTABILITY SYSTEM
19 FOR PUBLIC SCHOOLS; AND TO REMOVE PUBLIC
20 SCHOOLS FROM SCHOOL RATINGS FOR CERTAIN
21 SCHOOL YEARS.
22
23 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
24
25 SECTION 1. DO NOT CODIFY. TEMPORARY LANGUAGE.
26 (a) The General Assembly finds that:
27 (1) A change in the assessment system for public schools and
28 public school districts in Arkansas was necessary to align with the
29 educational priorities established by Acts 2023, No. 237, also known as the
30 "LEARNS Act";
31 (2) The development of a revised accountability system that
32 includes the new assessment system and better meets the needs of Arkansas
33 students is currently in progress; and
34 (3) A pause in new letter grade designations for the 2023-2024
35 and 2024-2025 school years under the existing school rating system will allow
36 the collection of necessary data to provide accurate and reliable
